{
  "stem": "20035.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And through the people from ORT and through-- through some American soldiers or through the UNRRA, we were able to buy stuff at the American Army store, which was outstanding not only value-wise, but we had to have the money to do it.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's the way we get it through ORT and through UNRRA, tremendous help.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I have a certificate even today from ORT which shows that I'm a teacher and-- teacher of what, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But anyway, they classified me with a picture, with a colored picture.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had American uniforms with all kind of false decoration on the arm that we should look similar to an American soldier.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it helped us to cross the borders, because we were afraid of nothing and nobody.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Basically nobody could do anything else, but what we could do is try to bring these little orphans on, try to give them some kind of comfort, what at-- what at that country or whatever they were.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was just nobody there and they were in a horrible, horrible mental, physical, or no parents, no nothing, I mean, some kind of love.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This kind of-- this kind of life went on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And finally, we were transferred to a place called Bayerisch Gmain.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Bayerisch Gmain, well, it's a tough time to spell, but I believe it's B-A-Y-E-R-I-C-H-- C-H-- C-S-H.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Gmain, the second word, is G-M-A-I-N.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is a-- this is a small town under-- almost at the Austrian border, right next to Bad Reichenhall.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
